  "description": "I want to look at encoding Moscow school of semiotics in Fennel. This is a continuation of Babble, [2025-09-16 Tue 18:25]. So, there are a few different structures in this school of semiotics, and they relate through various processes that rely on the structures having various conditions of various values.\nThis is a trickily specific way to describe it though, so let me go slow.\nThe structures I see are semiospheres, codes, signs (icons, indexes, symbols), text.\n",
